result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[MK] cases #16CM155, #16CM457, #16CM459 called at 3:33pm. 
Defendant Asia N Kelm in court with Attorney Karl E Huebner.  ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " No Contest " entered in Case #16CM457-Counts #1 & #2, and in Case #16CM459-; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified (ADA Hall submits a victim impact statement and restitution request in case #16CM457); the Court accepts the pleas, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgments of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Case #16CM155.

On Case #16CM457-Counts #1 & #2, and in Case #16CM459, the Court withholds sentence, and places Ms. Kelm on Probation for 18 months, with conditions:
--to undergo any assessment, treatment, or counseling as may be required by the Agent
--to attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program as supervised by the Agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision 
--a condition of Probation in Case #16CM457 only is:  to make restitution of $36 to Patience Olson; this amount is to be paid within 90 days 
--to pay costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge [clerk's calculation listed on the payment slip:  $453 on each count ($243 plus $200 plus $10)= $1359 plus $3.60 restitution process fee= $1362.60, to be paid to the Clerk of Courts Office within 60 days, or within 60 days Ms. Kelm is to arrange a payment plan with the Clerk of Courts Office).  

Days credit for time already served:  0 days
